menu "PMW3360 runtime behaviors"

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_RUNTIME_HOOKS
    bool
    default y
    help
      Build the weak runtime hook implementation used by the PMW3360 runtime
      tuning behaviors.

      Boards may override the hook with a strong symbol to trigger custom
      status updates or visual feedback whenever CPI or burst accumulation is
      changed at runtime.

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_CPI_CYCLE
    bool "PMW3360 CPI cycle behavior"
    default y
    depends on INPUT_PIXART_PMW3360
    help
      Expose a directly usable ZMK behavior that cycles PMW3360 CPI values at
      runtime.

      This behavior assumes a single enabled PMW3360 device in the build and
      is intended for keymap-level runtime tuning such as CPI up/down buttons.

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_BURST_ACCUMULATION_CYCLE
    bool "PMW3360 burst accumulation cycle behavior"
    default y
    depends on INPUT_PIXART_PMW3360
    help
      Expose a directly usable ZMK behavior that cycles the PMW3360 burst
      accumulation limit at runtime.

      This is primarily useful on BLE pointing builds where one-burst-per-HID-
      report can create visible report backlog under fast motion.

endmenu
